info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 25 at 4:31AM EST until January 25 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Mobile
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST EARLY THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Southwest winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph. * WHERE...In Alabama, Baldwin Inland, Baldwin Central and Baldwin Coastal Counties. In Florida, Escambia Inland, Escambia Coastal, Santa Rosa Inland, Santa Rosa Coastal, Okaloosa Inland and Okaloosa Coastal Counties. * WHEN...Until 6 AM CST early this morning. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
